cse:attribute.name: article.summary
cse:attribute.value: Tacloban was a city on the rise. In the first week of November, the city of 220,000 sat directly in the line of the most powerful storm ever recorded. Officials had days of warning and rushed to prepare. In the run-up to the storm, Philippine President Benigno Aquino III called on officials to ensure a "zero-casualty" event. As of Wednesday morning, the death toll from Typhoon Haiyan reached 5,500. Most of the dead were in Tacloban and the areas around it.
